  "content": "### 1. Emit Resolvable `to_file` from Tree-sitter\n### 2. Multi-Strategy Target Resolution in `wire_pipeline_relations()`\n\n## Benchmark Results\n\n**Baseline**: `benchmark-results/2026-03-04T04-48-57` (before fix)\n**After fix**: `benchmark-results/2026-03-04T06-59-58` (commit `0ace22b`)\n\n| Metric | Before | After |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Graph relations stored (ingest) | ~0 | **552** |\n| Graph edges (rebuilt) | ~0 | **324** |\n| Q1 graph_expanded | 0 | 0 |\n| Q2 graph_expanded | 0 | 0 |\n| Q3 graph_expanded | 2 | **6** |\n| Q4 graph_expanded | 1 | 1 |\n\n- Q1/Q2 remain at 0 because those queries match docs/config files with no code-level graph edges (expected behavior)\n- Q3 (cross-file code tracing) showed 3x improvement, confirming the wiring fix works\n- The infrastructure is validated: 552 relations stored during ingest proves CRATE_REF resolution + multi-strategy wiring works end-to-end\n\n\n## Future Work\n\n- **GraphRAG-Bench**: Integrate a systematic evaluation framework with ground-truth expected edges per query\n- **Python/JS relation improvements**: Extend `resolve_target_files()` with Python module resolution (`from . import utils`)\n- **Edge weight scoring**: Weight edges by relation type (imports vs implements vs contains) for better graph expansion ranking",
